  "texts": [
    "If an attack fails, it is a necessary condition to obtain a privacy-preserving algorithm.",
    "Nonetheless, the failure of attacks is not a sufficient condition, as a new attack may be proposed later, resulting in a higher lower bound.",
    "This shows that the privacy leakage of the algorithm had previously been underestimated.",
    "The bound provided by a DP analysis provides an upper bound, and the value of being close to 0 provides a sufficient condition for the algorithm to preserve privacy.",
    "However, attacks do provide insights into the sources of leakage in a system that handles data and can inform the calibration of mechanisms that provide DP guarantees, with the aforementioned caveats."
  ],
